{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"Included with: <b> δίκαιος</b> [ῐ], α, ον, <br /> also ος, ον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 901 (Lyric poetry), “IT” 1202, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 5.72 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: (δίκη): <br /><Level1><b>__A</b></Level1> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] and all writers, of persons, <b>observant of custom</b> or <b>rule,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.52 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; especially <b>of social rule, well-ordered, civilized,</b> ὑβρισταί τε καὶ ἄγριοι οὐδὲ δ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 9.175, compare 8.575; [Γαλακτοφάγοι] δικαιότατοι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.6; [Χείρων] δικαιότατος Κενταύρων 11.832, compare 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 314, 794 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; δ. πολίτης a <b>good</b> citizen, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 3.21, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>metaphorically</i> of the sea, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Solon Lyricus 12.2 (_superlative_)\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; δικαίη ζόη a <b>civilized</b> way of living, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.177. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <i>adverb</i> δικαίως, μνᾶσθαι woo <b>in due form, decently,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.90; ὑπὸ ζυγῷ λόφον δ. εἶχον \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<b>loyally,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 292. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.2</b></Level3> <b>observant of duty</b> to gods and men, <b>righteous,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.209, etc.; δ. πρὸς πᾶσαν ὁμιλίην 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἰητροῦ” 2; ἰθὺς καὶ δ. 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.96 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to δυσσεβής, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 598, compare 610; δ. καὶ ὅσιος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 507b; δικαίων ἀδίκους φρένας παρασπᾷς 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 791 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also of actions, etc., <b>righteous,</b> ἐπὶ ῥηθέντι δικαίῳ a thing <b>rightly</b> said, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.414, etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__A.3</b></Level3> ὁ δίκαιος, euphemistic of a sacred snake, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “GDI” 5056 (from Crete). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level1><b>__B</b></Level1> later: <br /><Level2><b>__B.I</b></Level2> <b>equal, even, well-balanced,</b> ἅρμα δίκαιον <b>evengoing</b> chariot, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.2.26: so _metaphorically_, νωμᾷ δικαίῳ πηδαλίῳ στρατόν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 1.86; δικαιόταται ἀντιρροπαί 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 7 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δικαιότατα μοχλεύειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. passage]: hence, \">Refs</a>]<b>fair, impartial,</b> βάσανος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 1.8; συγγραφεύς 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Hist.Conscr.” 39. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__B.I.b</b></Level4> <b>legally exact, precise,</b> τῷ δικαιοτάτῳ τῶν λόγων to speak <b>quite exactly,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.108, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.44 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of Numbers, αἱ ἑκατὸν ὀργυιαὶ δίκαιαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.149 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> -αίως, πάντα δ. ὑμῖν τετήρηται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.3; δ. ἐξετάζειν [prev. work]154. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.I.2</b></Level3> <b>lawful, just,</b> especially τὸ δ. <b>right,</b> opposed to τὸ ἄδικον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.96, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 189 (Lyric poetry), etc.; τὸ δ. τὸ νόμιμον καὶ τὸ ἴσον 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1129a34; δ. διορθωτικόν, διανεμητικόν, [prev. work] 1131b25, 27 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ πολιτικὸν δ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 1134b18; ἔστι ἐπιεικὲς τὸ παρὰ τὸν γεγραμμένον νόμον δ. [prev. author] “Rh.” 1374a27, compare “EN” 1137b12; καὶ δίκαια κἄδικα 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 99; τὰ ἴσα καὶ τὰ δ. 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.67 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τοὐμὸν δ. my own <b>right,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 810 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐλθεῖν ἐπὶ τοῦτο τὸ δ. bring the case to this <b>issue,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 6.24 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐδὲν τῶν δ. ποιεῖν τινί not to do <b>what is just and right</b> by a man, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 5.3.10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ δ. ἔχειν, λαμβάνειν, receive <b>one's due,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “An.” 7.7.14, 17 \">Refs</a>]; τὰ δ. πράττεσθαι πόλιν give a city its <b>deserts,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 812 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκ τοῦ δικαίου, ={δικαίως}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1435, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.89 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; so ἀπὸ τοῦ δικαίου, τῶν δικαίων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Inscription Prien.” 50.8 (2nd c.BC), 123.8 (1st c.BC)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; μετὰ τοῦ δ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 2.12, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.177 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ δίκαιον <b>lawful claim,</b> ἃ ἔχομεν δίκαια πρός.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.54, compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.179, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Lucullus” 3, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ πρὸς ἀλλήλους δ. mutual <b>obligations</b> or <b>contracts,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.21.10 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; ἐπὶ συγκειμένοις τισὶ δικαίοις on certain agreed <b>terms,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 3.51 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> <b>-αίως</b> <b>rightly, justly,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.137; μεῖζον ἢ δ. 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 376 (Lyric poetry); καὶ δ. καὶ ἀδίκως 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.135. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.II</b></Level2> of persons and things, <b>meet and right, fitting,</b> δ. τοῦδε τοῦ φόνου ῥαφεύς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1604; κόσμος οὐ φέρειν δ. [prev. author] “Eu.” 55 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἵππον δ. ποιεῖσθαί τινι make a horse <b>fit for</b> another's <b>use,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 4.4.5, compare “Cyn.” 7.4 (ἵππος δ. τὴν σιαγόνα\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] having a <b>good</b> mouth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 1.196). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__B.II.b</b></Level4> <b>normal,</b> σχήματα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 69; φύσις [prev. author] “Fract.” 1 (_superlative_). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.2</b></Level3> <b>real, genuine,</b> γόνος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” [1119]; ποιῶν τὰ ἐν τῇ τέχνῃ δ. “Supp.epigram” 2.184.7 (Tanagra, 2nd c.BC). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <i>adverb</i>, εἴπερ δικαίως ἐστ᾽ ἐμός <b>really and truly</b> mine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 547, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 418e. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__B.II.3</b></Level3> ὁ δ. λόγος the plea <b>of equity,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.76 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> <b>-αίως</b> <b>with reason,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 6.34, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 675 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> <b>-ότερον</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 1149, etc.;\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] also <b>-οτέρως</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 15.170 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i> <b>-ότατα</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1222 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Aeolic dialect</i> δικαίτατα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 12(2).526c17 (from Eresus). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.III</b></Level2> ψυχὴ ἐς τὸ δ. ἔβη 'the land of the leal', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 7.2543.3 (from Thebes). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level1><b>__C</b></Level1> in Prose, δίκαιός εἰμι, with <i>infinitive</i>, δίκαιοί ἐστε ἰέναι you <b>are bound</b> to come, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.60, compare 8.137; δ. εἰμεν ἔχειν [prev. author] 9.27 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δ. εἰμι κολάζειν I <b>have a right</b> to punish, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1434, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 400; δ. ἐστι περιπεσεῖν κακοῖς 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 3.3.7 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δ. εἰσι ἀπιστότατοι εἶναι they <b>have most reason</b> to distrust, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.17; δ. βλάπτεσθαι 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 20.12; δ. ἐστιν ἀπολωλέναι \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>dignus est qui pereat,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 6.37 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ὁ σπουδαῖος ἄρχειν δ. <b>has a right</b> to.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1287b12 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; with a non-personal subject, ἔλεος δ. ἀντιδίδοσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.40 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: less frequently in <i>comparative</i> and <i>superlative</i>, δικαιότεροι χαρίσασθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 20.34; δικαιότατος εἶ ἀπαγγέλλειν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 172b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but δίκαιόν ἐστι is also found, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.39, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 611, etc.: _plural_, δίκαια γὰρ τόνδ᾽ εὐτυχεῖν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1126, compare “Tr.” 495, 1116 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δικαίως ἄν, with <i>optative</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 276a. [δικαίων\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] with <i>penultimate</i> short in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.AD: Orphica “Fragmenta” 247.2 \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]; compare οὐ δίκαον· οὐ δίκαιον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus] \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1346","accentedUnicode":"δικαίως","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0091","matchingForm":"ἀδικέω","stepTransliteration":"adikeō","gloss":"to harm","_zh_tw_Gloss":"傷害","_es_Gloss":"maltratar","_zh_Gloss":"伤害"},{"strongNumber":"G0092","matchingForm":"ἀδίκημα","stepTransliteration":"adikēma","gloss":"crime","_zh_tw_Gloss":"不義","_es_Gloss":"crimen","_zh_Gloss":"不义"},{"strongNumber":"G0093","matchingForm":"ἀδικία","stepTransliteration":"adikia","gloss":"unrighteousness","_zh_tw_Gloss":"不義","_es_Gloss":"injusticia","_zh_Gloss":"不义"},{"strongNumber":"G0094","matchingForm":"ἄδικος","stepTransliteration":"adikos","gloss":"unjust","_zh_tw_Gloss":"不義","_es_Gloss":"injusto","_zh_Gloss":"不义"},{"strongNumber":"G0095","matchingForm":"ἀδίκως","stepTransliteration":"adikōs","gloss":"unjustly","_zh_tw_Gloss":"冤屈","_es_Gloss":"injustamente","_zh_Gloss":"冤屈"},{"strongNumber":"G0476","matchingForm":"ἀντίδικος","stepTransliteration":"antidikos","gloss":"opponent","_zh_tw_Gloss":"對頭","_es_Gloss":"adversario","_zh_Gloss":"对头"},{"strongNumber":"G1341","matchingForm":"δικαιοκρισία","stepTransliteration":"dikaiokrisia","gloss":"justice","_zh_tw_Gloss":"公義審判","_es_Gloss":"justicia ","_zh_Gloss":"公义审判"},{"strongNumber":"G1342","matchingForm":"δίκαιος","stepTransliteration":"dikaios","gloss":"just","_zh_tw_Gloss":"義人","_es_Gloss":"justo ","_zh_Gloss":"义人"},{"strongNumber":"G1343","matchingForm":"δικαιοσύνη","stepTransliteration":"dikaiosunē","gloss":"righteousness","_zh_tw_Gloss":"義","_es_Gloss":"justicia ","_zh_Gloss":"义"},{"strongNumber":"G1344","matchingForm":"δικαιόω","stepTransliteration":"dikaioō","gloss":"to justify","_zh_tw_Gloss":"稱義","_es_Gloss":"justificar ","_zh_Gloss":"称义"},{"strongNumber":"G1345","matchingForm":"δικαίωμα","stepTransliteration":"dikaiōma","gloss":"righteous act","_zh_tw_Gloss":"條例","_es_Gloss":"acto justo","_zh_Gloss":"条例"},{"strongNumber":"G1347","matchingForm":"δικαίωσις","stepTransliteration":"dikaiōsis","gloss":"justification","_zh_tw_Gloss":"稱義","_es_Gloss":"justificación ","_zh_Gloss":"称义"},{"strongNumber":"G1348","matchingForm":"δικαστής","stepTransliteration":"dikastēs","gloss":"magistrate","_zh_tw_Gloss":"審判官","_es_Gloss":"juez","_zh_Gloss":"审判官"},{"strongNumber":"G1349","matchingForm":"δίκη","stepTransliteration":"dikē","gloss":"condemnation","_zh_tw_Gloss":"刑罰, 天理","_es_Gloss":"condenación ","_zh_Gloss":"刑罚, 天理"},{"strongNumber":"G1738","matchingForm":"ἔνδικος","stepTransliteration":"endikos","gloss":"just","_zh_tw_Gloss":"該當, 該受","_es_Gloss":"justo ","_zh_Gloss":"该当, 该受"},{"strongNumber":"G2613","matchingForm":"καταδικάζω","stepTransliteration":"katadikazō","gloss":"to condemn","_zh_tw_Gloss":"定罪, 被定罪","_es_Gloss":"condenar","_zh_Gloss":"定罪, 被定罪"},{"strongNumber":"G5267","matchingForm":"ὑπόδικος","stepTransliteration":"hupodikos","gloss":"accountable","_zh_tw_Gloss":"審判","_es_Gloss":"responsable","_zh_Gloss":"审判"}],"shortDef":"- equitably","mediumDef":"equitably, justly, righteously","stepGloss":"rightly","stepTransliteration":"dikaiōs","count":5,"_es_Definition":"justamente, como es debido, debidamente, rectamente, virtuosamente (1TE.2:10) ","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) (法律上) 正直, 公平地<br>2) (性格,思想,行為上) 正直地, 公平地","_zh_Definition":"1) (法律上) 正直, 公平地<br>2) (性格,思想,行为上) 正直地, 公平地","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự công bình; sự công chính; theo pháp luật","_zh_tw_Gloss":"公義","_es_Gloss":"justamente ","_zh_Gloss":"公义"}]}